[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_6fcyd")
reagent_id = "HCl"
title = "Hydrochloric acid"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]HCl[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]36.5 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Liquid (solution)[/cell]
[cell]Type:[/cell][cell]Strong acid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
H₂ + Cl₂ → 2HCl  
H₂S + Cl₂ → 2HCl + S
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Highly acidic and very reactive.
• Corrosive to metals and tissues.
• Reacts with bases to form salt and water.
• Reacts with some metals to produce hydrogen gas.
[b]Where it is found[/b]
• In gastric juice in the human stomach.
• Produced industrially for chemical processes.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Cleaning metals (removing rust).
• Production of chlorides and other chemicals.
• Used in laboratories and industry.
[b]Safety[/b]
Strongly corrosive — can damage skin, eyes, and materials.
Vapors can irritate the respiratory system."
